radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal with no focal lesions. The kidneys are symmetric with one subtly hypoenhancing left kidney, cortical scarring, and multiple subcentimeter cysts. An appendicolith at the base of a dilated appendix measuring up to 1.3 cm, with adjacent fat stranding, consistent with acute appendicitis.
